<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Arms">Arms</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Beaufort,_1st_Earl_of_Somerset&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Arms"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>As a legitimised grandson of King Edward III, Beaufort bore that king's royal arms, differenced by a <i>bordure gobony argent and azure</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
<ul class="gallery mw-gallery-traditional center">
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Arms_of_John_Beaufort,_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_(Bastard).svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Early arms of John Beaufort with a bend dexter"><img alt="Early arms of John Beaufort with a bend dexter" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg/103px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="103" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg/154px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg/206px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset_%28Bastard%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="410" data-file-height="478" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Early arms of John Beaufort with a bend dexter</div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Arms_of_John_Beaufort,_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Beaufort arms (ancient): Royal arms of King Edward III within a bordure compony argent and azure"><img alt="Beaufort arms (ancient): Royal arms of King Edward III within a bordure compony argent and azure" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg/103px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg.png" decoding="async" width="103" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg/154px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg/205px-Arms_of_John_Beaufort%2C_1st_Earl_of_Somerset.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="598" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Beaufort arms (<a href="/wiki/Ancient_and_modern_arms" title="Ancient and modern arms">ancient</a>): <i>Royal arms of King Edward III within a bordure compony argent and azure</i></div>
		</li>
		<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
			<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px; height: 150px;"><span typeof="mw:File"><a href="/wiki/File:Beaufort_Arms_(France_modern).svg" class="mw-file-description" title="Beaufort arms (modern): Quarterly, 1st &amp; 4th: Azure, three fleurs de lis or (France); 2nd &amp; 3rd: Gules, three lions passant guardant in pale or (England); all within a bordure compony argent and azure[13]"><img alt="Beaufort arms (modern): Quarterly, 1st &amp; 4th: Azure, three fleurs de lis or (France); 2nd &amp; 3rd: Gules, three lions passant guardant in pale or (England); all within a bordure compony argent and azure[13]" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg/103px-Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg.png" decoding="async" width="103" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg/154px-Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg/205px-Beaufort_Arms_%28France_modern%29.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="512" data-file-height="598" /></a></span></div>
			<div class="gallerytext">Beaufort arms (<a href="/wiki/Ancient_and_modern_arms" title="Ancient and modern arms">modern</a>): <i>Quarterly, 1st &amp; 4th: Azure, three fleurs de lis or (<a href="/wiki/Royal_Arms_of_France" class="mw-redirect" title="Royal Arms of France">France</a>); 2nd &amp; 3rd: Gules, three <a href="/wiki/Lions_in_heraldry" class="mw-redirect" title="Lions in heraldry">lions passant guardant</a> in pale or (<a href="/wiki/Royal_arms_of_England" class="mw-redirect" title="Royal arms of England">England</a>); all within a bordure compony argent and azure</i><sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></div>
		</li>
</ul>
<p>Arms of Beaufort, legitimised progeny of John of Gaunt, third surviving son of King Edward III: <i>Royal arms of King Edward III within a bordure compony argent and azure</i> (see <a href="/wiki/Coat_of_arms_of_England" title="Coat of arms of England">Coat of arms of England</a>). The arms were updated when the kings of England adopted France modern, having been adopted by the King of France in 1376. <a href="/wiki/Charles_Somerset,_1st_Earl_of_Worcester" title="Charles Somerset, 1st Earl of Worcester">Charles</a>, an illegitimate son of <a href="/wiki/Henry_Beaufort,_3rd_Duke_of_Somerset" title="Henry Beaufort, 3rd Duke of Somerset">Henry Beaufort, 3rd Duke of Somerset</a> (1436–1464), took the surname "Somerset" together with the Beaufort arms and was created <a href="/wiki/Baron_Herbert" title="Baron Herbert">Baron Herbert</a> (1461) and <a href="/wiki/Earl_of_Worcester" title="Earl of Worcester">Earl of Worcester</a> (1513). In 1682 his descendant <a href="/wiki/Henry_Somerset,_3rd_Marquess_of_Worcester" class="mw-redirect" title="Henry Somerset, 3rd Marquess of Worcester">Henry Somerset, 3rd Marquess of Worcester</a> (1629–1700), was created <a href="/wiki/Duke_of_Beaufort" title="Duke of Beaufort">Duke of Beaufort</a>. These arms are thus used by Beaufort, Duke of Somerset (extinct) and Somerset, Duke of Beaufort (extant).
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Ancestry">Ancestry</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=John_Beaufort,_1st_Earl_of_Somerset&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: Ancestry"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
